news.title: Maharashtra govt clears Rs 600 crore cost escalation for Nagpur metro phase-I
news.para: The state cabinet on Tuesday approved increase in project cost from Rs8,680 crore to Rs9,279.6 crore citing increase in expenditure of land acquisition, construction of two additional stations (Airport South and Cotton Market) etc.

news.title: HC issues notice to state government over appointments of Gujarat REAT
news.para: The petitioner stated that in the absence of judicial and technical members in the appellate body of RERA, its functioning has been adversely affected and litigants have to knock on the doors of the high court.

news.title: Gujarat RERA orders civil custody of Pacifica Developers' MD, associates for disobeying orders
news.para: Not only did the builder not give the flat to the purchaser, he sold it to a third party despite a RERA's order. This led the authority to take action against the builder and three of his associates for disobedience of an order and for misguiding the authority.

news.title: Only 1% of large construction sites in Gurugram registers on portal for dust control
news.para: There are around 3,000 large construction sites in Gurugram but just 30 are on the portal. It's mandatory for construction sites bigger than 500sqm to install PM2.5 and PM10 sensors that send live feed to the portal, according to CAQM directives.

news.title: Builders want government to reduce stamp duty, table proposal before Maharashtra CM
news.para: Developers have made a demand to the state government to provide a partial waiver in stamp duty payment to boost sales of real estate in Maharashtra. The proposal was mooted on October 3 to Chief Minister Eknath Shinde.

news.title: IDBI Bank to seek bids via Swiss auction for Jaypee Infratech debt
news.para: Potential bidders will have to compete with the National Asset Reconstruction Co's (NARCL) ₹3,570-crore offer - the biggest to date by the government-backed bad bank.

news.title: Madhuri Dixit-Nene buys sea-view apartment in Mumbai's Worli for Rs 48 crore
news.para: The deals value the apartment at nearly Rs 90,000 per sq ft, pushing it in the tally of the largest deals for residential apartments in terms of value anywhere across the country so far this year.

news.title: Goisu Realty leases two plots in Mumbai's BKC for Rs 2,067 crore
news.para: "Goisu Realty Pvt Ltd, a unit of the Tokyo-headquartered Sumitomo Corporation, was the successful bidder for both plots," metropolitan commissioner S V R Srinivas said.

news.title: Rustomjee aims to raise Rs 450 crore for AIF investing in redevelopment projects by Nov
news.para: ​First of the investments to be done by the AIF christened 'Mt K Kapital' will be in realty projects undertaken by the group itself, Rustomjee's chairman and managing director Boman Irani told PTI.

news.title: New York City office leasing surges; still below pre-pandemic levels
news.para: Office leasing volume rose 27.6% to 9.23 million square feet, the strongest quarterly gain since the end of 2019 - a gangbuster year for leasing in New York, according to Colliers International Group Inc.

news.title: Australia's 'Big Four' lenders raise home loan rates in step with central bank
news.para: The move is in sync with the country's central bank, which earlier in the day raised its benchmark lending rate by 25 basis points. Australian banks have so far followed the steps of the Reserve Bank of Australia (RBA) in raising borrowing costs.

news.title: NGT directs Express Builders to pay Rs 15 crore compensation for illegal construction
news.para: ​​The green panel was hearing a petition against the violation of EC conditions by Express Builders and Promoters Private Limited in constructing 'Express Zenith' at Sector 77 in Noida.

news.title: Delhi RERA seeks pollution exemption for projects
news.para: The move comes after the CII Delhi Sub-committee on Real Estate and the Confederation of Real Estate Developers' Associations of India (CREDAI)-NCR submitted a representation to RERA of Delhi, UP and Gurgaon to exempt projects from the construction ban.

news.title: Indore: Over 40 residential structures to be razed for STP in Devnagar
news.para: He said that an STP with 35mld capacity has been planned in the area and work on the same is scheduled to be started after the Diwali festival.

news.title: Demolition drive will resume after Dasara: Karnataka revenue minister
news.para: Revenue minister R Ashoka, who held a meeting with BBMP and revenue department officials on Monday, said the drive was stopped because of festivities.
